properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 3 at 8:21AM MST until January 4 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Missoula MT
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected. Strongest winds will be along the Highway 93 corridor
from Eureka to Whitefish. Winds in high terrain will be in
excess of 70 mph or higher at times.

* WHERE...Highway 2 Kalispell to Libby, Highway 37 Eureka to
Libby, Highway 56 Bull Lake Road, and Highway 93 Eureka to
Whitefish.

* SNOW: Blowing snow will also be an issue in areas where snow is
falling and combines with strong winds, creating very low
visibility. Backcountry conditions will be hazardous.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 11 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM TO 11 PM MST SATURDAY
